Trump described himself as a "nationalist"[413] and his foreign policy as "America First."[414][415] He espoused isolationist, non-interventionist, and protectionist views.[416][417] His foreign policy was marked by praise and support of populist, neo-nationalist and authoritarian governments.[418] Hallmarks of foreign relations during Trump's tenure included unpredictability and uncertainty,[415] a lack of a consistent foreign policy,[419] and strained and sometimes antagonistic relationships with the U.S.'s European allies.[420]
